$ !SASROOT/sasv9.cfg

This config file contains default SAS → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options[options]. It is created along with the installation and is
re-created when SAS is updated. Therefore, changes made to this file are lost after an update.

In order to override options in this file, use → Linux/fhs/usr/local/SAS/SASFoundation/9_x/sasv9_local_cfg.

sa:
  → Linux/fhs/usr/local/SAS/SASFoundation/9_x
